bug.short_desc: batik jar issue: svg export breaks if icon present
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1228675 java stacktrace
Description of problem:
If an icon is present on a mindmap svg export fails. see attached stack trace and image.
Filed bug on freemind at sourceforge and learnt that it was missing some batik lib. Added batik-all to the list of jars in /usr/bin/freemind and svg works. patch attached.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
freemind.noarch 1.0.1-10.fc24
How reproducible:
Steps to Reproduce: 1. start freemind on F24 2. load Test.mm 3. File->Export->SVG 4. Error!
Actual results:
stack trace and empty gui error
Expected results:
an svg exported!
Additional info:
https://sourceforge.net/p/freemind/bugs/1266/
Created attachment 1228678 screenshot of freemind error dialog
